Charlists

<!-- livebook:{"break_markdown":true} -->

charlists are a blind spot because Ruby uses both " and ' for strings, but in Elixir they are different!

```elixir
<<99, 97, ?t>>

```



```elixir
[99, 97, 116]

```

```elixir
'cat'
```

```elixir
"cat" == ~c"cat"
```

```elixir
[99, 97, 116]
```
